Two factors directly contribute to the amount of specular reflectance loses at a material interface: (i) the angle of incidence θ1 of the incoming THz beam; and (ii) the index of refraction n mismatch between air (n1) and the sample material (n2). The relationship between these entities can be computed using Snell’s Law, n1sin θ1= n2sin θ2, where θ1 is the angle of incidence in air (n1 ≈ 1), and θ2 is the angle of refraction in the material (n2). Neglecting polarization, the magnitude of specular reflectance can be approximated using the Fresnel relation:
